webwork.pg-code:
Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->are(n => 'Real');
$f = Formula("(2^n-1)/2^(n-1)");

$radio = RadioButtons([
  "The sum with powers of ${BM}\frac12${EM} is larger.",
  "The sum with powers of ${BM}\frac14${EM} is larger.",
  "The two sums are equal."
  ], 0
);

$radio2 = RadioButtons([
  "The sum with powers of ${BM}\frac12${EM} is larger.",
  "The sum with powers of ${BM}-\frac12${EM} is larger.",
  "The two sums are equal."
  ], 0
);

Context("Fraction");

solution.p:
We can tell that as the denominator grows, the missing piece coming from the numerator being 1 too few is getting smaller and smaller. As n\to\infty, that missing piece is heading toward 0. Another way to see that is to actually divide
\frac{2^n - 1}{2^{n-1}} = \frac{2^n}{2^{n-1}} - \frac{1}{2^{n-1}} = 2-\frac{1}{2^{n-1}}
As n\to\infty, we see that S_n\to 2.
